id: pm-n2ts
title: Add files discovery subcommand for referenced paths
description: "Add a pm files subcommand that scans item text for existing workspace/global path references, reports candidates, and can add missing linked files without duplicates."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: files,governance,pm-cli,traceability
created_at: "2026-04-25T20:08:23.573Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-25T21:10:59.270Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "pm files can discover referenced files from item body/comments/notes/learnings and other text context, skip already linked files, validate file existence/containment, support dry-run/reporting and apply modes, and include detailed end-to-end tests in sandboxed temporary projects."
parent: pm-5rjn
resolution: Implemented pm files discover with dry-run candidate reporting and --apply linked-file backfill.
expected_result: "Referenced project and global file paths in item text are discovered, existing linked files are skipped, and apply mode adds only missing links with history."
actual_result: "Runtime, CLI, contracts, Pi wrapper, completion, docs, unit coverage, and temporary-project end-to-end coverage are implemented and verified."
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-25T20:08:23.573Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'files referenced linked files comments body learnings' --limit 10; pm search 'pm files scan referenced paths linked file hygiene' --limit 10; pm search 'linked-file hygiene referenced files comments body' --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20; pm list-blocked --limit 20. Net-new because related linked-file hygiene and check-files items are closed and do not implement a files command scanner/backfill path."
  "2026-04-25T20:45:56.709Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: implemented pm files discover <ID> dry-run reporting and --apply backfill for existing project/global file paths found in item text. Duplicate protection normalizes linked paths and skips already linked entries. Verification passed: focused unit/contract/wrapper/completion suite (123 tests), temporary-project CLI e2e (1 passed / 61 skipped), full regression (76 files / 1042 tests), coverage (100% statements/branches/functions/lines), pm test pm-n2ts --run --progress (4/4 linked commands passed), pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift, and pm validate --check-files --scan-mode tracked-all."
  "2026-04-25T21:10:59.270Z",codex-agent,"Post-close evidence update: after tightening absolute path line-suffix sanitization and increasing the existing core lifecycle integration timeout for stable V8 coverage under load, verification passed again: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test (76 files / 1042 tests) and node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (76 files / 1042 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-25T20:08:23.573Z",codex-agent,Implementation should keep pm mutations authoritative by applying additions through the existing files mutation path and preserving duplicate checks against normalized linked file paths.
